text.section:
As used in this chapter:
"Bank" and "depository" include any qualified financial intermediary and savings and loan associations chartered by the State of Kentucky or the United States government designated to take custody of state funds on deposit, for periods greater than overnight, with the intent to honor presentments against those deposits;
"Warrant" means a printed or electronic authorization from the Finance and Administration Cabinet for the Treasurer to issue a check;
"Form" or "report" means any written method of transporting data; and
"Writing" or "written" means letters, words, or numbers, or their equivalent, set down by handwriting, typewriting, printing, photostating, photographing, magnetic impulse, mechanical or electronic recording, or other form of data compilation.
